criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Systemic health (absence of Hypertension and Diabetes);

          -  Indication of dental extraction of at least 2 teeth (with at least 2/3 of bone
             support, in the region of premolars or molars with indication for extraction;

          -  Signature of the consent form;

          -  Individuals over 18 years old.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of periodontal disease at the time of surgery;

          -  Pregnant and lactating women;

          -  Smokers;

          -  Be under orthodontic treatment;

          -  Use medication that alters the bone healing process, such as those used to treat
             osteoporosis and the bisphosphonates group;

          -  Individuals under 18 years old.
